              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 13 Mar. 2020&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPARTMENT OF MEDICAL EDUCATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VACANCY NO: FM/MED 1/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PART – TIME CLINICAL SKILLS TUTORS (3 POSITIONS)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties:&lt;/strong&gt; The successful applicants should be able to; &lt;strong&gt;(i) &lt;/strong&gt;demonstrate basic clinical skills (communication and hand skills) to undergraduate medical students; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; examine the same skills as examiners in OSCEs (objective structured clinical exams). The part-time work will take up no less than 1½ hours and no more than 6 hours per week, for a maximum of 32 weeks per year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; The applicants should: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; Have at least an undergraduate medical degree (MBChB or MBBS); &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; Provide evidence of at least 3 years’ postgraduate medical practice; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; Experience in teaching clinical skills will be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/strong&gt; The University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualification&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to apply:&lt;/strong&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the university determine their suitability for the position.  They should provide current CV’s (including telephone and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, and THREE (3) reference letters.  Applicants should inform their referees to:  &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; Quote the position applied for and&lt;strong&gt; (ii)&lt;/strong&gt; submit their references directly to the address below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email to nkangana@mopipi.ub.bw &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to Faculty of Medicine, &lt;strong&gt;UB Teaching Hospital, 3rd Floor, Office F 4003&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NB:  Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
